<article class="h-entry post post--brief">
<h2 class="p-name post__title"><a href="/blog/2022/blog-posts-up-to-date/">Blog posts are up to date</a></h2>
<p class="post__byline">
By
<span class="p-author h-card">
<span class="p-name">Phil Gyford</span>
on
<time class="dt-published" datetime="2022-12-04 13:45:51">2022-12-04</time>
</p>
<div class="e-summary">
<p>The blog posts are now all up to date and should, hopefully, continue to be so, following <a href="https://ooh.directory/blog/2022/blog-posts-arent-updating/">the recent interruption in service</a>. The server now has more memory, the lucky thing.</p>
</div>
</article>
<article class="h-entry post post--brief">
<h2 class="p-name post__title"><a href="/blog/2022/blog-posts-arent-updating/">Blog posts aren&#x27;t updating</a></h2>
<p class="post__byline">
By
<span class="p-author h-card">
<span class="p-name">Phil Gyford</span>
on
<time class="dt-published" datetime="2022-12-03 17:55:55">2022-12-03</time>
</p>
<div class="e-summary">
<p>You might have noticed that no new posts are being added to the site at the moment. For example, the <a href="https://ooh.directory/updated/">Recently updated blogs page</a>&nbsp;isn't changing. This is because I moved another website to the same server as ooh.directory but that appears to be too much for it ‚Äì the task that runs every few minutes to fetch new blog posts now quits, bringing down the database with it. Consequently, there won't be any new posts appearing until the VPS gets upgraded a little. Shouldn't be too long.</p>
</div>
</article>
<article class="h-entry post post--brief">
<h2 class="p-name post__title"><a href="/blog/2022/first-two-days/">The first two days</a></h2>
